She wouldn't do that to her body & I'd never ask it. It's also messy and uncomfortable, and it would disrupt far too much of the rest of our lives.

Kids have turned out OK so far. As much as any kids do, and better than most. We spend a lot of time with them and teach by example most every day that life is weird, our bodies are weird, embrace the weird. It's weird. It's normal. It's fun. Not a lot of time in life to waste it on freaking out over normal shit.

I broke my finger almost two years, skin was split so bad you could see the bone. Hurt like a motherfucker. Went into the house, washed it up in the sink and 'sort of' put hings into 'sort of' the right place, taped the finger to the one next to it for support, called the hospital & told them I was driving over to get it taken care of. Kids & wife are right there with me all the way to the emergency room, watched the doctors shoot my hand up with pain meds and set it and stitch it up.

Everybody was curious about exactly how to fix something like that. Minimal drama, lots of jokes, everybody learned lots of shit that day. Normal life event, nothing to freak out over, 0/10 would NOT DO again if I had the choice. But, if it did happen again, would do it exactly the same way. It's the only way.
